@NODE bank "SuperMemo World's Database Bank"

All  users  of  SuperMemo  software  are  kindly  invited to send in their
SuperMemo databases. Upon no-cost evaluation, the qualified databases will
be  added  to  the  SuperMemo  World's Database Bank and distributed along
other  SuperMemo  World  products. All authors of qualified databases will
receive  their royalties on terms agreed with SuperMemo World (standardly,
10%  of the end-user price of the database). Alternatively, databases that
are  most  promising  from the commercial standpoint can be purchased from
the  author  (s)  outright.  The  most  soughtafter subjects are: English,
sciences,  medicine, technology, political and social sciences, economics,
and  geography.  Your  chances  of  positive  database evaluation increase
greatly  if  you use it by yourself, and can send them in the native form,
i.e.,  with  your  learning  process  included, so that such parameters as
factor   distribution,  interval  distribution,  burden,  etc.,  could  be
inspected.

All databases sent for evaluation will automatically enter the Annual Best
Database  Competition  with attractive prizes in cash and in kind (closing
December 31 each year). See DBANK.TXT for a database registration coupon.
@ENDNODE



@NODE acqrate "Acquisition rate"

acquisition rate - speed of learning. Usually expressed in items memorized
per  year per minute. For example, if 20 minutes a day yield 10, 000 items
a  year,  the  acquisition  rate  is 500 items/year/min. In SuperMemo, the
acquisition rate may vary from 100-1000 depending on the difficulty of the
material,  @{" forgetting index " link forgindex}  and  the  stage of the process (acquisition
rate  may  substantially  decrease  in  the  first  year  of the process).
@ENDNODE

@NODE answer "Answer"

answer - (1) second part of the SuperMemo  @{" item " link item}.  (2) Option on the main
menu  of the learn and random test windows that can be used to display the
answer.
@ENDNODE

@NODE afield "Answer field"

answer  field  -  part of the SuperMemo editing window where the answer is
displayed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE agrade "Average grade"

average grade -  @{" trailing average " link trailav}  of  @{" response qualities " link respqual}  provided
during repetitions.  It is displayed in learning parameters as grade.
@ENDNODE

@NODE curint "Current interval"

current  interval  - number of days between the last repetition of a given
item and the date of the next repetition.
@ENDNODE

@NODE db "Database"

database - (1) collection of items. (2) Collection of 4-6 files that store
a  database  and  all information pertaining to the learning process (e.g.
memorized, forgetting curves, etc.).
@ENDNODE

@NODE dispers "Dispersal procedure"

dispersal  procedure - procedure used to modify the length of intervals in
@{" dispersion of intervals " link dispint}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE dispint "Dispersion of intervals"

dispersion of intervals -  random  modification  of  @{" optimal  intervals " link optint}
used  to speed up the  @{" optimization " link optimiz}  and to reduce the  @{" lumpiness " link lump}  of
item-to-day assignments.
@ENDNODE

@NODE edwdw "Editing window"

editing window - window such as edit, learn or search window in which such
operations  of the editing mode as: edit, delete, select, print, memorize,
reset, etc. are available.
@ENDNODE

@NODE editwdw "Edit window"

edit window - one of the  @{" editing windows " link edwdw},  which  is  displayed  upon
choosing Database:Edit on the main menu.
@ENDNODE

@NODE drill "Final drill"

final  drill  - third part of the learn option when repetitions pass again
through  items  that  scored less than 4 in response quality assessment in
the two previous parts (outstanding repetitions and memorizing new items).
@ENDNODE

@NODE forgindex "Forgetting index"

forgetting  index  -  proportion  of  items that are not remembered at the
moment  of  repetition.  In  SuperMemo  3.0,  it may be programmed to vary
between 3% and 20%,  and is displayed in  @{" learning parameters " link lp}  as lapses
(<number>).   In  the  main  window,  the measured value of the forgetting
index  is  displayed to the right of the requested value of the forgetting
index.
@ENDNODE

@NODE intactitem "Intact item"

intact  item  -  item  that  has not yet been memorized by means of option
learn or memorize. Intact items do not take part in repetitions.
@ENDNODE

@NODE intactq "Intact queue"

intact queue - sequence of  @{" intact items " link intactitem}  that await memorization.  This
sequence is the same as the sequence of introducing items to the database.
@ENDNODE

@NODE interfer "Interference"

interference - (in SuperMemo) problems with remembering an item due to its
similarity or close relationship with another item or items.
@ENDNODE

@NODE interval "Interval"

interval - period between two successive repetitions expressed in days.
@ENDNODE

@NODE item "Item"

item  -  simple  question-answer  pair  used  to  represent  knowledge  in
SuperMemo.
@ENDNODE

@NODE irp "Item and repetition parameters"

item   and   repetition   parameters   -  collection  of  parameters  that
characterize the item currently displayed in one of the editing windows.
@ENDNODE

@NODE knolret "Knowledge retention"

knowledge  retention  -  proportion  of  knowledge  retained  in memory as
a result of learning.  In SuperMemo,  depending on the  @{" forgetting index " link  forgindex}
the  knowledge  retention  may  vary from 85% to 99% (compare retention at
repetitions).
@ENDNODE

@NODE lp "Learning parameters"

learning  parameters  -  parameters  pertaining  to  the learning process,
displayed in the main window of SuperMemo.
@ENDNODE

@NODE learnwdw "Learn window"

learn  window  - one of the editing windows which is used to present items
during repetitions in option learn.
@ENDNODE

@NODE lump "Lumpiness"

lumpiness  -  tendency of item memorized on the same day to stick together
in  the  learning  process. Lumpiness results in substantial variations of
the  number  of  items  that  are  to  be repeated on particular days. The
problem of lumpiness was eliminated in SuperMemo versions above 3 by means
of the dispersion of intervals.
@ENDNODE

@NODE measfindex "Measured forgetting index"

measured forgetting index -  @{" forgetting index " link forgindex}  measured in the course of
repetitions.   It  is  displayed  as lapses in learning parameters (to the
right  from  the  value  of  the  requested  forgetting  index  placed  in
parentheses).
@ENDNODE

@NODE memo "Memorization"

memorization - process in which items are memorized, i.e. committed to the
learner's memory.
@ENDNODE

@NODE memorized "Memorized"

memorized  - (in learning parameters) number of items in the database that
have already been memorized.
@ENDNODE

@NODE memoitem "Memorized item"

memorized item - item that has already been memorized.
@ENDNODE

@NODE memlapse "Memory lapse"

memory lapse - instance of forgetting an individual item.
@ENDNODE

@NODE mininfo "Minimum information principle"

minimum  information  principle - principle of the SuperMemo method saying
that items should be as simple in form as possible.
@ENDNODE

@NODE mnemo "Mnemonics"

mnemonics  -  art of representing knowledge in a graphic, easy to remember
way.  It  may  greatly increase the learner's ability to memorize numbers,
intricate names, symbols, formulas, etc.
@ENDNODE

@NODE optint "Optimal interval"

optimal  interval - (1) interval that yields the forgetting index equal to
the requested value, i.e., equal to lapses. (2) (In repetition parameters)
newly computed value of the optimal interval.
@ENDNODE

@NODE optimiz "Optimization"

optimization  -  (in  SuperMemo)  process  by  which the set of factors of
individual  items, are modified in order to yield the desired retention at
repetitions.
@ENDNODE

@NODE outitem "Outstanding item"

outstanding  item  -  (in  the  Learn option) items that are scheduled for
repetition  on  the present and all the previous days on which repetitions
have not been made.
@ENDNODE

@NODE outrep "Outstanding repetitions"

outstanding  repetitions  -  repetitions scheduled for the current and all
outstanding days.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ques "Question"

question - first part of the SuperMemo item.
@ENDNODE

@NODE qfield "Question field"

question  field  -  part  of  a  editing window where the question part of
a SuperMemo item is displayed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE rep "Repetition"

repetition  -  act  of answering a question in the learn option (including
memorization of new items).
@ENDNODE

@NODE repcycle "Repetition cycle"

repetition  cycle - series of activities performed during repetitions: (1)
displaying  the  question,  (2) answering the question, (3) displaying the
answer, (4) providing the grade, and (5) requesting the next repetition.
@ENDNODE

@NODE repsched "Repetition schedule"

repetition  schedule - a particular way in which repetitions are spaced in
time.
@ENDNODE

@NODE repspace "Repetition spacing"

repetition spacing - see @{" spacing of repetitions " link spacerep}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE reptime "Repetition time"

repetition  time  -  time (in seconds) needed for a repetition of a single
item; measured from the moment of displaying the question to the moment of
displaying the answer.
@ENDNODE

@NODE reqfindex "Requested forgetting index"

requested forgetting index -  @{" forgetting index " link forgindex}  requested  for  a  given
database  (in  Miscellaneous:Parameters).   It is displayed in parentheses
aside  Lapses  in  learning  parameters (to the left from the value of the
measured forgetting index).
@ENDNODE

@NODE respo "Response"

response  -  recalled  form  of  the  correct  answer that appeared in the
learner's mind in the course of a repetition (compare answer).
@ENDNODE

@NODE respqual "Response quality"

response  quality  -  (also  grade)  number from the range 0-5 that is the
learner's  score  for  the  accuracy  of  his response, i.e., how well the
response matches the answer.
@ENDNODE

@NODE reten "Retention"

retention -  see  @{" knowledge  retention " link knolret}.  (2)  (In  learning  parameters)
estimation  of  knowledge  retention  based on the value of the forgetting
index.
@ENDNODE

@NODE sess "Session"

session  -  single  workout  with a SuperMemo database which starts at the
moment of using open and ends with closing the database with save.
@ENDNODE

@NODE spaceeff "Spacing effect"

spacing  effect - (in psychology) observation that longer inter-repetition
intervals  produce  better  memories  (up to a certain limit determined by
forgetting).
@ENDNODE

@NODE spacerep "Spacing of repetitions"

spacing   of  repetitions  -  unique  pattern  in  which  inter-repetition
intervals  are  chosen  in learning. Spacing of repetitions may be massed,
distributed, or, like in SuperMemo, progressive.
@ENDNODE

@NODE spsched "Sparse schedule"

sparse schedule -  @{" repetition  schedule " link repsched}  in  which  repetitions  are
relatively infrequent.
@ENDNODE

@NODE sm "SuperMemo"

SuperMemo - (1) see @{" SuperMemo method " link smmet}. (2) Computer program implementing
the SuperMemo method.
@ENDNODE

@NODE smmet "SuperMemo method"

SuperMemo  method - speed-learning method developed by Polish biologist P.
A.  Woúniak  and promoted world-wide by SuperMemo World. SuperMemo greatly
increases  the rate of knowledge acquisition (speed of learning) at a high
level of knowledge retention by means of optimum repetition spacing.
@ENDNODE

@NODE trailav "Trailing average"

trailing average - kind of moving average which is defined as follows:

	a(n) = s(n)*f + a(n-1)*(1-f)

where:

a(n) - trailing average of an n-long sequence of numbers,
s(n) - n-th number in the sequence,
f    - a fraction such that 0<f<1.
@ENDNODE



